        "Answer": "The defense raised by Amante is error in personae. This defense is not proper because of Article 4 of the Revised Penal Code, which provides that a person committing a felony is liable criminally although the wrongful act done be different from the unlawful intent. Thus, under this provision, Amante is liable for the wrongful act done, and that is child abuse against Alisto, although it differs from the wrongful act intended, and that is abusing Aliswan."
