        "Question": "A killed his wife and buried her body in their backyard. Ten years later, a care-taker found the bones and reported the matter to the police. A was subsequently arrested. Is A's defense of prescription of the crime tenable? Explain.  (2010 Bar Question)",
        "Answer": "No, the defense of prescription of the crime is not tenable. The crime committed is parricide which prescribes in twenty (20) years (Art 90, RPC). It was only when the care-taker, Z, found the victim's bones and reported the matter to the police that the crime is deemed legally discovered by the authorities or their agents and thus the prescriptive period of the crime commenced to run."
