        "Question": "Dancio, a member of a drug syndicate, was a detention prisoner... Brusco, another member of the syndicate, regularly visited Dancio. Edri, the guard in charge who had been receiving gifts from Brusco... became relaxed in the inspection of his belongings... Brusco... smuggled in a pistol which Dancio used to disarm the guards and destroy the padlock... enabling Dancio to escape. What crime(s) did Dancio, Brusco and Edri commit? Explain. ",
        "Answer": "Dancio committed the crime of direct assault under Article 148 for disarming the guards with the use of pistol while they are engaged in the performance of their duties... Edri committed infidelity in the custody of prisoner or evasion through negligence under Article 224... By accepting gifts from Brusco... he is also guilty of indirect bribery under Article 211. Brusco committed delivery of prisoner from jail under Article 156, qualified by his bribery of Edri."
