        "Question": "Rigoberto gate-crashed the 71st birthday party of Judge Lorenzo. Armed with a piece of wood... Rigoberto hit Judge Lorenzo on the back... Judge Lorenzo had cited Rigoberto in contempt and ordered his imprisonment for three (3) days two years earlier. Is Rigoberto guilty of Direct Assault? Why or why not?  (2009 Bar Question)",
        "Answer": "No, Rigoberto is not guilty of Direct Assault because Judge Lorenzo has ceased to be a judge when he was attacked. He has retired (71 yrs. old) from his position as a person in authority when he was attacked. Hence, the attack on him cannot be regarded as against a person in authority anymore."
