        "Question": "X, without intent to kill, aimed his gun at Z and fired it, hitting the latter who died as a consequence. Under the circumstances  (A) X cannot plead praetor intentionem since the intent to kill is presumed from the killing of the victim. (B) X may plead praetor intentionem since he intended only to scare, not kill Z. (C) X may plead aberratio ictus as he had no intention to hit Z. (D) X may plead commission of only Discharge of Firearm as he had no intent to kill Z when he fired his gun.",
