        "Answer": "[a] Delito continuado refers to a crime constituted by several overt acts committed by the offender in one place, at about the same time, and all such overt acts violate one and the same provision of penal law, thus demonstrating that all such acts are the product of a single indivisible criminal resolution. [b] No. His contention is not tenable. The 500 acts of estafa do not constitute a single or continuing crime of estafa. Each act of issuing a check to each investor constitutes a separate crime of estafa. The fact that the checks were issued at about the same time and in one place does not make it a continuing crime because each act of estafa is a complete crime in itself, affecting different victims."
