        "Answer": "OFW committed three counts of murder qualified by treachery, if the killing was done in a manner that ensured the victims had no chance to defend themselves. The mitigating circumstances of voluntary surrender and confession may be appreciated. The aggravating circumstance of dwelling may be applied if the killing was done in the home of the victims. However, passion and obfuscation may not be considered as a mitigating circumstance because it was not based on a lawful cause (the affair alone may not be sufficient). The penalty should be imposed considering the mitigating and aggravating circumstances."
